From: Nikolay Borisov <nik.borisov@suse.com>
Date: Thu, 13 Nov 2025 13:05:45 +0200
Subject: Fix xsaves_xsavec_checked kABI breakage
References: git-fixes
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI fix

Changing kvm_hv causes the kABI checker to consider kvm_x86_ops to have changed.
This is safe because kvm_x86_ops is being initialized to either svm_x86_ops or
vmx_x86_ops via kvm_initi()->kvm_init_arch() with a simple assignment. It's
used to abstract the SVM/VMX specific ops from the core kvm code.

Signed-off-by: Nikolay Borisov <nik.borisov@suse.com>
Reviewed-by: Michal Koutný <mkoutny@suse.com>
---
 arch/x86/include/asm/kvm_host.h |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/kvm_host.h
+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/kvm_host.h
@@ -773,8 +773,9 @@ struct kvm_hv {

 	/* How many vCPUs have VP index != vCPU index */
 	atomic_t num_mismatched_vp_indexes;
-
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
 	bool xsaves_xsavec_checked;
+#endif
 };

 enum kvm_irqchip_mode {
